    "costs": "2675",
    "actions_taken": [
      "Safety stand down with all personnel involved in running casing",
      "Well monitored on trip tank during safety stand down",
      "Employee sent to shore for medical evaluation",
      "Incident reported to BSEE New Orleans District"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 20, 2020 at 10:00 hours, a joint of 10.75 inch casing fell out of the elevators into the V-Door while the Nabors 202 drill crew was running casing into the well at Mississippi Canyon 194. The elevators contacted the derrick A-frame, compromising their integrity and causing the casing joint to be dislodged. The falling casing struck another joint in the V-Door, causing it to slide out onto the walkway and pipe rack. One employee sustained a minor injury when tripping while moving away from the area. Damage included two sections of handrail and one tote tank totaling $2,675.",
